Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools include Reports and Dashboards, Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards, CRM Analytics, Intelligent Analytics Apps, Tableau, Unified Analytics Experiences, Einstein Discovery.

Einstein Discovery helps detect bias in data, allowing you to remove its distorting effects on analysis and predictions. Bias indicates variables are treated unequally in the model.

Required editions include Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, available with CRM Analytics for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions, also available in Developer Edition.

Examples of bias include proxy variables and disparate impact.

To detect and remove bias:

*   Select a variable suspected to indicate bias and click Analyze for Bias.
*   Click Update Model to create a new model version.
*   Filter the list by clicking the shield button to view insights associated with sensitive variables.
*   Investigate your model's insights to decide whether to include or exclude a sensitive variable.

Einstein Discovery shows disparate impact analysis and potential bias analysis.
title: Detecting and Removing Bias from Models
